    "introduction": "Born in Scotland's capital Edinburgh in 1984, Tony McGeever quickly became accustomed at a very early age to the theatrical world by appearing in Cameron Mackintosh's Oliver and Joseph and His Amazing Technicolour Dream Coat. Years later he went on to study at the world renowned Royal Scottish Conservatoire, formally Royal Scottish Academy of Music and Drama, going on to appear in award winning productions for the RSC, National Theatre and Dundee Rep. He has appeared on television for the BBC and ITV in numerous credits, such as the Emmy award winning British series Accused by Jimmy McGovern.",
